# Linux Fundamentals

## Introduction

Linux is a free and open-source operating system widely used in servers, cloud computing, cybersecurity, embedded systems, and enterprise environments.

Many of the world's websites, cloud platforms, and security tools run on Linux-based systems.

Understanding Linux is considered a fundamental skill in cybersecurity because security professionals frequently interact with Linux servers, networks, and security tools.

# Personal Reflection

While studying Linux fundamentals, I learned how operating systems manage files, users, processes, and system resources.

I also gained experience with basic Linux commands and developed an understanding of why Linux is widely used in servers, cloud computing, and cybersecurity environments.

Learning Linux strengthened my understanding of how systems operate and provided practical skills that are valuable for cybersecurity and technology-related fields.

